<h2 id="section-top">Podiatry</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1629">Guy's and St Thomas' NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent23b5a8b74851454b993417d8fe7eb180">
</div>
<p>For general information about our podiatry services, see <a href="http://www.guysandstthomas.nhs.uk/our-services/therapies/foot-health/overview.aspx" target="_blank" title="foot health services">foot health services</a> on our website.</p>
<p><strong>Community services</strong></p>
<p>Guy’s and St Thomas' community podiatry service provides expertise in preventing / treating disorders of the foot and ankle to patients registered with GPs in Lambeth and Southwark.  </p>
<p>Treatment is based on clinical need and patients can self refer to the service. Individualised care plans are created and may be provided in community health clinics or patients' homes for those who are completely housebound. </p>
<p>The broad philosophy of clinical podiatric management is to: </p>
<ul>
<li>relieve pain</li>
<li>promote self care where appropriate</li>
<li>maintain function and mobility</li>
<li>prevent or minimise deformity</li>
<li>reduce the risk of ulceration and amputation </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Southwark residents</strong></p>
<p>A completed application form, available from our clinics or your GP, needs to be faxed / posted or delivered in person to any of our clinics.</p>
<p>For further information, please see <a href="http://www.guysandstthomas.nhs.uk/resources/patient-information/therapies/foot-health/southwark-foot-health-service.pdf" target="_blank" title="Southwark foot health service">Southwark foot health service</a>. </p>
<p><strong>Lambeth residents</strong></p>
<p>A completed application form needs to be faxed / emailed / posted to the customer service centre at Ackerman Health Centre or delivered in person to any of our clinics.</p>
<p>For further information, please see <a href="http://www.guysandstthomas.nhs.uk/resources/patient-information/therapies/foot-health/lambeth-foot-health-service.pdf" target="_blank" title="Lambeth foot health service">Lambeth foot health service</a>.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
